### Identifying and Scoping a New Revenue Opportunity

**Competencies:** [strategy] [initiative] [analysis] [communication]
**Role types:** [strategy] [biz-ops] [corpdev] [product] [chief-of-staff]

**Situation:** At Initech, our core product served mid-market companies but the sales team kept fielding inbound interest from enterprise accounts with fundamentally different needs. There was no formal product track or pricing for them, and these deals kept stalling or closing at heavy discounts.

**Action:** I pulled 18 months of CRM data to quantify the pattern, then interviewed six of the stalled accounts to understand their specific objections. I synthesized the findings into a two-page brief that identified three enterprise-specific requirements: SSO, audit logs, and dedicated SLAs. I presented the brief to the CEO and CPO with a recommended sequencing for adding these capabilities and a rough revenue model showing $2.1M in ARR opportunity from the existing pipeline alone.

**Result:** The brief became the basis for a formal enterprise tier, which launched eight months later. Within the first year, it contributed $1.6M in new ARR. My analysis was cited in the board deck for our Series C.

**30-second version:** At Initech, the sales team kept losing enterprise deals but nobody had mapped why. I pulled CRM data, ran customer interviews, and identified three capability gaps blocking the segment. My brief to the CEO turned into the product roadmap for a new enterprise tier that drove $1.6M ARR in year one and was cited in the Series C board deck.
